title: Understanding SQL Query Execution
text: In SQL, executing a query means running the command you have written to retrieve or manipulate data in the database.

title: Locating the Run Button
text: The Run button is typically located in the toolbar of your SQL editor. It is used to execute the query you have typed.

title: Executing the Query
text: To execute the query you have typed, you need to press a specific button in your SQL editor.
choices: Press the Save and Run button.
